{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-js","path":"/content/openapi/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Before jumping into my opinionated guide to client generation, I'd first like to take a moment to explain breifly, what an http client <em>is</em>.\nIn order to define this, let's break it down into two separate definitions (as silly as it may seem).</p>\n<h3>What is HTTP</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.w3schools.com/whatis/whatis_http.asp\">HTTP</a> is a protocol / procedure that web services follow to send and receive data from one another.</p>\n<div class=\"mermaid\" data-processed=\"true\"><svg id=\"mermaid-1590444837231\" width=\"671.578125\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" height=\"74\" viewBox=\"0 0 671.578125 74\"><style>#mermaid-1590444837231 .label{font-family:'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial;font-family:var(--mermaid-font-family);color:#333}#mermaid-1590444837231 .label text{fill:#333}#mermaid-1590444837231 .node rect,#mermaid-1590444837231 .node circle,#mermaid-1590444837231 .node ellipse,#mermaid-1590444837231 .node polygon,#mermaid-1590444837231 .node path{fill:#ECECFF;stroke:#9370db;stroke-width:1px}#mermaid-1590444837231 .node .label{text-align:center}#mermaid-1590444837231 .node.clickable{cursor:pointer}#mermaid-1590444837231 .arrowheadPath{fill:#333}#mermaid-1590444837231 .edgePath .path{stroke:#333;stroke-width:1.5px}#mermaid-1590444837231 .edgeLabel{background-color:#e8e8e8;text-align:center}#mermaid-1590444837231 .edgeLabel rect{opacity:0.5}#mermaid-1590444837231 .cluster rect{fill:#ffffde;stroke:#aa3;stroke-width:1px}#mermaid-1590444837231 .cluster text{fill:#333}#mermaid-1590444837231 div.mermaidTooltip{position:absolute;text-align:center;max-width:200px;padding:2px;font-family:'trebuchet ms', verdana, arial;font-family:var(--mermaid-font-family);font-size:12px;background:#ffffde;border:1px solid #aa3;border-radius:2px;pointer-events:none;z-index:100}#mermaid-1590444837231 .actor{stroke:#ccf;fill:#ECECFF}#mermai